<?xml version="1.0"?>
<rdf:RDF xmlns="https://purl.org/eudpp#"
     xml:base="https://purl.org/eudpp"
     xmlns:owl="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#"
     xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#"
     xmlns:xml="http://www.w3.org/XML/1998/namespace"
     xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#"
     xmlns:om-2="http://www.ontology-of-units-of-measure.org/resource/om-2/"
     xmlns:rdfs="http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#"
     xmlns:skos="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#"
     xmlns:vann="http://purl.org/vocab/vann/"
     xmlns:eudpp="https://purl.org/eudpp#"
     xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/">
    <owl:Ontology rdf:about="https://purl.org/eudpp/LCA">
        <owl:versionIRI rdf:resource="https://purl.org/eudpp/LCA/1.9.7"/>
        <dcterms:contributor xml:lang="en">Marc-Andree Wolf</dcterms:contributor>
        <dcterms:creator xml:lang="en">CIRPASS-2 Consortium</dcterms:creator>
        <dcterms:description xml:lang="en">
LCA (Life Cycle Assessment) module of an EU DPP (Digital Product Passport) core ontology proposal of the CIRPASS-2 European project.

SCOPE
This module is derived from the ILCD+EPD v1.3 data format (https://indatawg.github.io/ILCD-EPD-Data-Format/) and covers environmental-performance metadata that a DPP needs to carry. It supports both (a) general LCA studies of any product, expressed via eudpp:LCAStudy, and (b) Environmental Product Declarations (EPDs) conforming to EN 15804+A2 with EF 3.1 characterisation, expressed via eudpp:EPDStudy (a subclass of LCAStudy). The scope is deliberately lean: only metadata required for unambiguous identification of the study, its compliance status (where applicable), and its headline LCIA results (eudpp:LCIAResult: characterised impact results) and aggregated inventory-indicator results (eudpp:InventoryIndicatorResult: per-indicator aggregates per EN 15804+A2 Table 5) per life-cycle module and per scenario are modelled. Note that eudpp:InventoryIndicatorResult represents the AGGREGATED inventory-indicator value as printed in EN 15804+A2 EPD tables (e.g. total kg of HWD across A1-A3); it is NOT the raw flow-level life-cycle inventory (LCI) of a process. Full ILCD+EPD elements that are not needed for DPP use cases (exchanges/elementary flows, scenario quantities, variability/safety-margins sub-blocks, normalisation/weighting, characterisation-factor tables, etc.) are intentionally omitted in this release. Some fields from ILCD+EPD that describe the declared product rather than the LCA study (product identifiers, content declaration, service-life sub-structure) are handled by sibling modules of the CIRPASS-2 DPP core ontology (P_DPP, SOC) and are not redefined here.

NAMESPACE
All terms in this module live under the family-wide EUDPP namespace https://purl.org/eudpp# (matching ACTOR, P_DPP, SOC, CONNECTOR). The ontology IRI itself is https://purl.org/eudpp/LCA. There is no per-module term prefix.

PROVENANCE OF TERMS
Every class, property and named individual in this ontology carries an eudpp:ilcdSource annotation with one of: &quot;ILCD base&quot; (originates from the ILCD 1.1 base data format), &quot;ILCD+EPD extension&quot; (originates from the ILCD+EPD v1.3 extension, i.e. the epd, epd2, epd24 namespaces of InData), &quot;LCA ontology extension&quot; (introduced by this module without direct ILCD/ILCD+EPD counterpart), or &quot;LCA ontology metadata&quot; (annotation properties used internally by this module). This allows downstream systems to distinguish which parts of the ontology are generic LCA metadata and which are EPD-specific.

DEPENDENCIES
This module imports the ACTOR module of the CIRPASS-2 EU DPP Core Ontology (https://purl.org/eudpp/ACTOR) for its eudpp:Actor and eudpp:Facility classes. It also references, but does not import, the Ontology of Units of Measure (OM-2; http://www.ontology-of-units-of-measure.org/resource/om-2/) for units. Cross-module object properties whose domain is in this module and whose range is in another EUDPP module (Actor, Facility, Product, DPP) are NOT defined here; per the EU DPP Core Ontology design principles, they are defined in the CONNECTOR module. The full list of Connector entries that this module expects is given in the per-class comments below.

HARD-CODED INDICATOR SETS
Two indicator sets are declared as named individuals: (i) 37 EN 15804+A2 EF 3.1 indicators (13 core impact + 6 impact with-caveats + 18 resource-use, waste and output-flow inventory indicators), used by EN 15804+A2 EPDStudy instances; and (ii) 16 EF 3.1 / PEF impact categories, used by general LCAStudy instances following the EU Environmental Footprint method. The two sets overlap in concept but differ in operational form (EN 15804+A2 splits Climate change into four sub-indicators and selects a different &quot;with caveats&quot; subset; EF 3.1 keeps the 16 PEF categories at one level of aggregation). Additional LCIA methodologies and results can be added by instantiating eudpp:LCIAOrInventoryMethod and eudpp:LCAResult (or its subclasses eudpp:LCIAResult and eudpp:InventoryIndicatorResult) without modifying this ontology.

REFERENCE
For more information, see Maigre, R., Haav, H.-M., Robal, T., Wolf, M.-A., and Danash, F. (2025). Ontology Requirements Specification for an EU DPP Core Ontology Proposal (1.1). CIRPASS-2 Consortium. https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.15270342
    </dcterms:description>
        <dcterms:issued rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">2026-04-27</dcterms:issued>
        <dcterms:license rdf:resource="https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0"/>
        <dcterms:license xml:lang="en">This ontology is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0. In case of dispute over Apache 2.0 applicability, or in case considering the ontology as a document, this ontology document is to be considered licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0).</dcterms:license>
        <dcterms:title xml:lang="en">LCA module of the CIRPASS-2 EU DPP Core Ontology</dcterms:title>
        <vann:preferredNamespacePrefix>eudpp</vann:preferredNamespacePrefix>
        <vann:preferredNamespaceUri>https://purl.org/eudpp#</vann:preferredNamespaceUri>
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">The LCA module of the EU DPP core ontology, version 1.9.7.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">EU DPP LCA</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:seeAlso rdf:resource="https://indatawg.github.io/ILCD-EPD-Data-Format/"/>
        <rdfs:seeAlso rdf:resource="https://standards.cen.eu/dyn/www/f?p=204:110:0::::FSP_PROJECT:65243"/>
        <owl:priorVersion rdf:resource="https://purl.org/eudpp/LCA/1.9.6"/>
        <owl:versionInfo>1.9.7</owl:versionInfo>
    </owl:Ontology>
    


