    <owl:AnnotationProperty rdf:about="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel"/>
    


    <!-- https://purl.org/eudpp#ilcdSource -->

    <owl:AnnotationProperty rdf:about="https://purl.org/eudpp#ilcdSource">
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Provenance annotation identifying whether a class, property or named individual of this ontology originates from the ILCD base data format (&quot;ILCD base&quot;), from the ILCD+EPD v1.3 extension i.e. the epd / epd2 / epd24 namespaces of InData (&quot;ILCD+EPD extension&quot;), is introduced by this LCA module without direct ILCD counterpart (&quot;LCA ontology extension&quot;), or is internal annotation metadata of this module (&quot;LCA ontology metadata&quot;). Annotation property; does not affect reasoning.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">ILCD source</rdfs:label>
        <ilcdSource>LCA ontology metadata</ilcdSource>
    </owl:AnnotationProperty>
    


    <!-- https://purl.org/eudpp#unitAsString -->

    <owl:AnnotationProperty rdf:about="https://purl.org/eudpp#unitAsString">
        <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Human-readable label of the unit in which the associated EN 15804 indicator value is expressed, e.g. &quot;kg CO2-eq&quot;, &quot;MJ, net calorific value&quot;, &quot;m3&quot;. Annotation property (not for automated unit arithmetic).

Pattern for resolving to a machine-readable OM-2 Unit individual (two-step lookup):
STEP 1 - Retrieve the set of Unit individuals in the Ontology of Units of Measure (OM-2, base IRI http://www.ontology-of-units-of-measure.org/resource/om-2/). Each Unit individual carries (i) an rdfs:label (the unit&apos;s long English name, e.g. &quot;kilogram&quot;), (ii) an om:symbol datatype property (the standard symbol, e.g. &quot;kg&quot;), and typically (iii) an om:alternativeSymbol or om:alternativeLabel with variants.
STEP 2 - Match the string stored in eudpp:unitAsString against OM-2 via rdfs:label, om:symbol, or om:alternativeSymbol as appropriate. Compound EN 15804 units such as &quot;kg CO2-eq&quot; or &quot;mol H+-eq&quot; are not directly represented as single OM-2 Unit individuals; they should be decomposed (mass in kg, normalized via a characterisation vector) or mapped to an application-specific extension of OM-2. For simple indicators (e.g. FW in m3, SM in kg, HWD in kg, MJ), direct lookup against OM-2 Unit individuals with matching om:symbol works.

Authoritative OM-2 release: om-2.0.rdf, see https://github.com/HajoRijgersberg/OM. Note that the OM-2 property names given here (rdfs:label, om:symbol, om:alternativeSymbol) are stable across the OM 2.0 release. Downstream implementers should verify the exact OM-2 property IRIs against the OM-2 release they use.</rdfs:comment>
        <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">unit as string</rdfs:label>
        <ilcdSource>LCA ontology metadata</ilcdSource>
    </owl:AnnotationProperty>
    


